23/03/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) arrested a former Bosnian Muslim commander Monday (March 22nd) for war crimes committed against Croatian civilians and prisoners of war during the 1992-1995 conflict.
Hasan Hakalovic, 63, commanded a unit operating in the village of Trusina and allegedly failed to punish subordinates who committed war crimes.
Bosnian Muslim units attacked Trusina in 1993, killing 22 people.
(RTRS, Srna, Fena, BHRT, Nezavisne Novine - 22/03/10)
